- You don't eat this, you bury it.
- That's a home-made lunch.

05:13.380 --> 05:15.870
Your old lady drag her carcass
out of bed for you?

05:16.010 --> 05:19.130
- She does it first day of school.
- Big deal.

05:21.470 --> 05:24.050
- Kenickie. Over here.
- Where you at?

05:25.100 --> 05:26.850
We're right here.

05:26.980 --> 05:29.650
- Where were you all summer?
- Are you my mother?

05:29.770 --> 05:33.190
- Just askin'.
- Working. More than you can say.

05:33.320 --> 05:36.740
- Working?
- Yes, lugging boxes at Bargain City.

05:36.870 --> 05:39.240
- Nice job.
- Eat me.

05:39.370 --> 05:41.330
I'm saving up to get me some wheels.

05:41.450 --> 05:43.200
- Wanna hear what I did?
- No.

05:43.330 --> 05:45.540
Hey, there's Danny.

05:46.380 --> 05:48.420
Danny! Danny!

06:02.270 --> 06:04.350
You seen any new broads there?

06:04.480 --> 06:08.020
Nah, same old chicks,
everybody's made them.

06:08.150 --> 06:10.230
So what'd you do all summer?

06:10.360 --> 06:13.030
I was hanging around at the beach.
You know.

06:13.160 --> 06:16.080
It's tough with all those chicks
hanging around you.

06:16.200 --> 06:20.250
The only thing
that hangs around you are the flies.

06:20.380 --> 06:23.410
How was the action
at the beach, man?

06:23.710 --> 06:26.040
Whew. It was flipping.

06:26.170 --> 06:27.920
Yeah? Crazy?

06:28.050 --> 06:32.430
I did meet this one chick.
She was sorta cool.

06:32.560 --> 06:34.720
You mean she puts out?

06:34.850 --> 06:38.020
Come on, Sonny,
is that all you think about?

06:38.150 --> 06:40.850
- Freakin' A.
- (bell)

06:42.490 --> 06:44.110
Hey, guys, wait up.

06:44.240 --> 06:47.020
- Do I look OK, Frenchy?
- Sure, you look good.

06:47.160 --> 06:50.490
- I'm really nervous.
- You look terrific.

06:50.620 --> 06:54.530
- So, this is Rydell?
- Yep. You'll love it.

06:54.670 --> 06:58.500
I loved the last school I was at.
I wish I was there right now.

06:58.630 --> 07:01.120
Still, I'm no stranger to heartbreak.

07:01.260 --> 07:03.580
Why? You got psoriasis?

07:06.890 --> 07:08.380
(car backfires)

07:21.700 --> 07:23.740
Well, here we are again.

07:23.870 --> 07:27.780
- But this time we're seniors.
- We're gonna rule the school.

07:27.910 --> 07:29.790
(all laugh)

07:29.920 --> 07:31.740
Jan, that is so adolescent.

07:31.880 --> 07:35.410
- We are adolescent.
- We don't have to flaunt it.

07:35.550 --> 07:37.090
OK, girls.

07:37.220 --> 07:38.960
Let's go get 'em.

07:44.930 --> 07:47.180
Blanche, do you have
the new schedules?

07:47.310 --> 07:50.020
Yes, Miss McGee,
I just had my hands on them.

07:50.150 --> 07:53.020
Oh, good, they'll be
nice and smudged.

07:53.150 --> 07:56.900
Here we are. If it had been a snake,
it would've bitten me.

07:58.280 --> 08:01.620
These are the schedules
we couldn't find last semester.

08:01.750 --> 08:04.200
Next year,
you might find this semester's.

08:12.130 --> 08:16.080
- I've got Kenickie again.
- He's been here longer than I have.

08:16.220 --> 08:20.470
First day of school and already
my castor oil is missing.

08:21.440 --> 08:24.010
How many days
till Christmas vacation?

08:24.150 --> 08:25.260
86.

08:25.400 --> 08:27.360
- 86?
- And counting.

08:29.150 --> 08:31.560
- Can I help you?
- Yes, it's my first day.

08:31.700 --> 08:35.280
- I'm not sure where I should be.
- Welcome to Rydell.

08:35.409 --> 08:38.200
You'll have to fill out
these forms, but...

08:38.330 --> 08:41.000
Excuse me a minute.
I'll be right back.

08:42.840 --> 08:47.170
- Do you have a pencil, please?
- Yes, dear. There you are.

08:48.050 --> 08:49.550
(bell)

08:56.690 --> 09:00.440
Jeez. Every teacher I got this year
has flunked me at least once.

09:00.570 --> 09:03.020
You'll spend your time
in McGee's office.

09:03.150 --> 09:07.320
- She'll wish she'd never seen me.
- Yeah? And what are you gonna do?

09:07.450 --> 09:11.360
I just ain't gonna take her crap.
I don't take no crap from nobody.

09:11.500 --> 09:13.790
- Sonny?
- Oh, hello, ma'am.

09:13.920 --> 09:17.000
- Shouldn't you be in home room?
- I was going for a walk.

09:17.130 --> 09:19.290
- You were dawdling.
- Yes, ma'am.

09:19.420 --> 09:22.960
That is no way to start
a new semester, Mr LaTierri.

09:23.090 --> 09:24.500
(mutters in Italian)

09:24.640 --> 09:29.180
Perhaps a session of banging erasers
after school would put you on track.

09:29.310 --> 09:30.770
Yes, ma'am.

09:30.890 --> 09:34.730
- Do you plan to stand there all day?
- No, ma'am. I mean, yes.

09:34.860 --> 09:36.770
- Well, which is it?
- No, ma'am.

09:36.900 --> 09:39.140
- Good. Then move.
- Yes, ma'am.

09:41.740 --> 09:44.580
I'm glad you didn't take
any of her crap, Sonny.

09:44.700 --> 09:46.530
You would have told her off, huh?

09:46.660 --> 09:49.750
Mr LaTierri.
Yes, ma'am, no, ma'am...

09:49.870 --> 09:50.870
Hey, Eugene.

09:51.000 --> 09:52.990
How you doin'?

09:53.130 --> 09:55.370
- Shake, buddy.
- (buzzing)

09:55.920 --> 09:58.590
What's wrong?
You're wearing glasses.

09:58.720 --> 10:00.800
- I got an astigmatism.
- Too bad.

10:04.180 --> 10:08.100
(students) # As I go travelling down
life's highway

10:08.650 --> 10:13.270
# Whatever course my fortunes
may foretell...

10:14.450 --> 10:16.850
(chimes)

10:17.990 --> 10:21.690
Good morning, boys and girls.
Welcome to what we're sure will be

10:21.830 --> 10:23.950
our greatest year at Rydell.

10:24.080 --> 10:27.500
Saturday night will be
our first pep rally and bonfire.

10:27.630 --> 10:30.200
I want to see all of you students
out there,

10:30.340 --> 10:35.090
with plenty of support for Coach
Calhoun and the Rydell Rangers.

10:35.220 --> 10:39.380
If you can't be an athlete,
be an athletic supporter.

10:40.020 --> 10:42.340
And now for the really good news.

10:42.480 --> 10:44.470
One of the most exciting things

10:44.610 --> 10:47.310
to ever happen at Rydell High.

10:47.440 --> 10:50.230
National Bandstand television show

10:50.360 --> 10:54.830
has selected Rydell as
a representative American high school

10:54.950 --> 10:58.570
and will do a live broadcast
from our very own gym.

10:58.710 --> 11:00.330
(cheering)

11:00.460 --> 11:03.290
It is our chance
to show the entire nation

11:03.420 --> 11:06.090
what fine, bright, clean-cut,

11:06.220 --> 11:10.340
wholesome students
we have here at Rydell.

11:11.300 --> 11:12.630
(screams)

11:19.360 --> 11:20.900
# Ba, ba, bamba

11:21.020 --> 11:22.980
