- How's it hangin'?

42:48.180 --> 42:50.170
OK, the meeting is in session.

42:53.100 --> 42:57.180
Know what I heard? Last year the fuzz
had Thunder Road staked out.

42:57.320 --> 43:01.610
- Everyone got hauled to the clink.
- No one'll catch Greased Lightning.

43:01.740 --> 43:04.030
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

43:05.070 --> 43:08.410
- Somebody snaking you, Danny?
- Bite the weenie, Rizz.

43:08.540 --> 43:10.450
With relish.

43:14.880 --> 43:18.790
- I don't know about these chicks.
- They're only good for one thing.

43:19.470 --> 43:23.550
What do you do with 'em
the other 23 hours 45 minutes a day?

43:24.470 --> 43:26.130
Does it only take 1 5 minutes?

43:28.940 --> 43:31.230
Want some new music?

43:31.360 --> 43:34.030
- Yeah.
- I'll need some money.

43:36.990 --> 43:38.900
Thanks.

43:42.200 --> 43:44.030
(wolf whistles)

43:45.120 --> 43:46.950
I'll be right back.

43:52.420 --> 43:54.250
Hi, Danny!

43:55.260 --> 43:57.930
- I can't talk.
- What are you doing later?

43:58.050 --> 44:00.630
- I can't talk, alright?
- Call me.

44:11.400 --> 44:13.560
- Hi, Sandy.
- Oh, hi.

44:13.700 --> 44:15.940
- How are you?
- Fine, thanks.

44:16.080 --> 44:17.540
That's good.

44:17.660 --> 44:21.160
Sandy, I've been wanting
to talk to you for a long time.

44:21.290 --> 44:24.290
- What about?
- About the night at the bonfire.

44:24.420 --> 44:26.790
The way I acted, that was terrible.

44:26.920 --> 44:30.130
It wasn't me, you gotta know that.

44:30.260 --> 44:32.830
It was me, of course,
but it wasn't me.

44:34.430 --> 44:37.220
You see, Sandy,
I got this image, right? And...

44:37.350 --> 44:40.770
That's why I'm so glad
that Tom's such a simple person.

44:45.490 --> 44:48.690
Simple's right.
Too bad his brains are in his biceps.

44:49.780 --> 44:51.410
Jealous, are you?

44:52.490 --> 44:55.990
Jealous? Oh, come on, Sandy,
don't make me laugh.

44:57.290 --> 44:59.330
What have you ever done?

45:02.920 --> 45:05.790
Come on! I can run circles
around those jerks.

45:05.930 --> 45:08.090
I'll believe that when I see it.

45:32.130 --> 45:36.450
Let's start with the first rule. Cut
it down to two packs a day. There.

45:40.340 --> 45:43.710
What sort of athletics
are you interested in?

45:43.850 --> 45:44.930
You like the rings?

45:45.060 --> 45:49.270
Yeah, I installed a set
just a couple of weeks ago.

45:51.190 --> 45:54.310
The first thing we have to do
is you have to change.

45:54.440 --> 45:56.570
That's why I'm here, to change.

45:56.700 --> 46:00.030
- No, I mean your clothes.
- Oh.

46:06.750 --> 46:08.790
Alright. Let's knock it off.

46:08.920 --> 46:14.620
Fellas, I wanna introduce a new man.
Danny. Let's give him a tryout.

46:16.970 --> 46:20.890
- Better watch it.
- Come on. A little fire, here we go.

46:34.570 --> 46:36.530
You have to dribble.

46:40.080 --> 46:42.160
- Here you go, Coach.
- Thanks, son.

46:42.290 --> 46:44.660
Dribble the ball,
put it in the basket.

46:44.790 --> 46:47.790
- Think you can do that?
- Can I do that!

46:47.920 --> 46:50.960
- OK.
- Danny, over here. Danny!

46:51.090 --> 46:52.640
Let's go.

46:55.060 --> 46:56.970
That's it. Go, go, go.

46:57.730 --> 46:59.390
Get him, Danny.

47:03.900 --> 47:05.610
- (whistle)
- What'd I do?

47:05.740 --> 47:08.490
- Is he kidding?
- Boy, oh, boy.

47:11.530 --> 47:16.450
I want you to meet
your wrestling partner. Danny, Andy.

47:18.290 --> 47:20.040
Are you crazy?

47:20.170 --> 47:23.370
Come on, come on.
Let's start. Get in first position.

47:23.510 --> 47:25.750
Danny, you get down.

47:25.880 --> 47:28.260
OK, Andy, get down. Ready?

47:31.020 --> 47:32.640
(whistle)

47:33.810 --> 47:35.350
Hold it, hold it.

47:36.230 --> 47:39.100
Danny, you gotta try. Come on.

47:40.610 --> 47:44.310
Alright, Andy, let's change
positions. You get down. Come on.

47:49.450 --> 47:51.330
Alright. Ready?

47:51.460 --> 47:53.170
(whistle)

47:54.380 --> 47:56.120
- Give?
- Yeah, give.

47:56.250 --> 47:57.580
Good.

48:02.720 --> 48:03.720
He's a hitter.

48:07.520 --> 48:11.350
You'll like baseball. It's not
that much of a contact sport.

48:11.480 --> 48:13.940
Get in there and let's see
what you can do.

48:14.070 --> 48:16.020
Throw the ball. Let's play.

48:17.570 --> 48:19.310
Let's pitch this guy out.

48:19.450 --> 48:22.200
- He can't hit.
- This boy can't even bat.

48:22.330 --> 48:25.330
- Strike.
- I told you. He doesn't even swing.

48:25.460 --> 48:28.160
What kind of ball player are you?
Put it in here.

48:30.750 --> 48:32.500
Strike.

48:33.880 --> 48:37.550
Come on. A little fire in there.
Let's see you hit it.

48:41.720 --> 48:43.550
Foul ball.

48:46.310 --> 48:48.560
- Easy, easy.
- Now! Come on.

48:48.690 --> 48:50.850
Put the bat down. Put the bat down.

48:52.570 --> 48:56.070
There's a lot of other sports
that don't have any contact.

48:56.200 --> 48:58.910
- Yeah, like what?
- Like track.

48:59.040 --> 49:02.540
- What do you mean, running?
- Just like running?

49:03.500 --> 49:05.870
I mean something
that needs endurance.

49:06.000 --> 49:10.800
Something that needs stamina.
Like, long-distance running.

49:10.930 --> 49:13.170
Cross-country running.

49:15.510 --> 49:17.760
- That could be cool.
- Good.

49:44.720 --> 49:45.960
Danny.

49:49.930 --> 49:52.170
Danny, are you alright?

49:54.310 --> 49:56.140
Danny, talk to me.

49:57.190 --> 50:00.720
The least you can do is talk to me
after the way you treated me.

50:00.860 --> 50:03.650
The way I... ?
Sandy, I told you I was sorry.

50:03.780 --> 50:05.520
Got you talking.

50:07.030 --> 50:09.700
- You sure you're OK?
- Yes, I'm fine.

50:11.290 --> 50:14.290
- So, still dating that jockstrap?
- Well...

50:15.590 --> 50:19.500
- Is he taking you to the dance?
- Well, that all depends.

50:19.630 --> 50:21.170
- On what?
- On you.

50:21.300 --> 50:23.260
- On me?
- Yeah.

50:23.600 --> 50:25.090
He can stag it.

50:31.020 --> 50:32.560
Come on.

50:32.690 --> 50:34.180
(horn)

50:35.190 --> 50:37.230
(music plays in background)

50:44.250 --> 50:47.660
- Sandy, let's go someplace else.
- Why?

50:49.790 --> 50:51.830
We can't be alone here, that's why.

50:51.960 --> 50:53.540
Danny.

50:55.300 --> 50:56.840
OK.

51:04.810 --> 51:06.770
You nearly pulled my arm out.

51:06.900 --> 51:09.980
I didn't want to miss this table.
It's the best one.

51:11.070 --> 51:14.150
- What are you doing?
- I just want privacy.

51:14.280 --> 51:17.700
- What'll it be, kids?
- Cherry soda, please.

51:17.830 --> 51:19.780
- Danny?
- I'm not very hungry.

51:19.910 --> 51:24.290
Give me a double polar burger with
everything and a soda with ice cream.

51:24.420 --> 51:26.460
Sounds good. I'll have the same.

51:26.590 --> 51:28.750
The same? You can eat a lot.

51:28.880 --> 51:31.250
- You're funny.
- No, you are.

51:31.380 --> 51:35.630
- How ya doing, Zuke? Nice!
- Hiya, Rizzo. How are you?

51:35.760 --> 51:37.920
Peachy keen, jelly bean.

51:38.390 --> 51:41.600
You got any quarters?
We could split an Eskimo Pie.

51:41.730 --> 51:45.980
- My Dutch treat days are over.
- You plan on staying home a lot.

51:46.110 --> 51:49.730
Greetings, pals and gals.
Anybody got 23 cents?

51:49.860 --> 51:52.320
Wanna chip in for a Dog-Sled Delight?

51:52.450 --> 51:56.700
I don't know where my money goes.
A dime here, 1 5 cents there.

51:56.830 --> 51:59.950
In a couple of months
Frenchy can take us all out.

52:00.080 --> 52:01.830
A working girl with income.

52:01.960 --> 52:05.050
Y'know, they don't pay
that much to start with.

52:05.170 --> 52:09.220
It's more than we make. Ante up,
I don't get my allowance till Friday.

52:09.350 --> 52:11.840
- You get an allowance?
- When I'm a good boy.

52:11.970 --> 52:14.550
Viola, a Dog-Sled Delight
with four spoons.

52:14.690 --> 52:17.560
- And an Eskimo Pie with a knife.
- Hi, gang.

52:19.480 --> 52:21.640
Here you are. Grab it and growl.

52:25.740 --> 52:28.070
I got so many hickeys
I look like a leper.

52:28.200 --> 52:32.250
Cheer up. A hickey from Kenickie
is like a Hallmark card.

52:32.370 --> 52:34.610
You care enough
to send the very best.

52:36.250 --> 52:39.540
- You pig.
- I love it when you talk dirty.

52:40.970 --> 52:44.880
My parents want to invite you
to tea on Sunday. Will you come?

52:46.060 --> 52:49.260
- I don't like tea.
- You don't have to drink tea.

52:50.150 --> 52:52.180
Well, I don't like parents.

52:54.610 --> 52:56.980
- Want some?
- Erm, uh-uh.

52:57.110 --> 52:59.070
You sure are a cheap date.

52:59.200 --> 53:02.230
- I didn't mean it like that.
- I understand.

53:02.370 --> 53:05.870
- I always found you understanding.
- I am.

53:06.000 --> 53:09.910
I also think
there's more to you than just fat.

53:10.040 --> 53:12.750
- Thanks.
- You're welcome.

53:12.880 --> 53:14.920
- Got a date for the dance-off?
- No.

53:15.050 --> 53:16.250
- Wanna go?
- Yeah.

53:16.380 --> 53:21.090
I'll be a senior forever if
I don't study for that algebra test.

53:21.220 --> 53:24.090
You're in luck.
You got an armed escort home.

53:24.230 --> 53:28.390
It's not the arms I'm worried about,
Sonny. It's the hands.

53:28.520 --> 53:30.520
She loves me.

53:32.570 --> 53:34.860
- You coming, French?
- I don't think so.

53:34.990 --> 53:38.070
- I think I'll hang out a bit longer.
- Alright.

53:38.200 --> 53:43.080
I have been dieting all day long. My
mom's apple pie's better than this.

53:43.210 --> 53:45.450
- Do you want a piece?
- Yeah, sure.

53:46.540 --> 53:47.870
- Putzie.
- Yeah?

53:48.000 --> 53:49.630
1 5 minutes!

53:51.050 --> 53:55.380
I'm worried about this dance-off. Do
they dance differently to back home?

53:55.510 --> 53:59.130
Don't worry.
Maybe we'll invent the Kangaroo Bop.

54:01.060 --> 54:03.100
Let's get out of here, Sandy.

54:03.230 --> 54:04.770
See you later.

54:05.530 --> 54:07.680
- Bye, Frenchy.
- See ya, Sandy.

54:10.240 --> 54:13.530
Great. I'm stuck with the check.
Give me money.

54:14.490 --> 54:18.440
OK, what's with you tonight?
You got the personality of a wet mop.

54:18.580 --> 54:22.660
- Don't start with me.
- Fine. How about I finish with ya?

54:23.460 --> 54:25.460
Finish this!

54:26.510 --> 54:28.050
To you from me, Pinky Lee.

54:30.890 --> 54:32.800
Sorry, French.

54:37.560 --> 54:40.230
(distant) Hey, Rizzo.
I want to talk to you!

54:43.070 --> 54:45.230
No use crying over spilt milk shake.

54:45.360 --> 54:47.110
Oh, I'll be OK.

54:48.830 --> 54:50.870
You know it's near closing time?

54:51.000 --> 54:53.070
Do you mind if I stay a bit longer?

54:53.210 --> 54:55.200
No, suit yourself.

54:55.330 --> 54:57.790
- Wow.
- What?

54:57.920 --> 55:01.290
I hate to tell you, but your
hair looks like an Easter egg.

55:02.180 --> 55:04.000
Oh, yeah.

55:04.140 --> 55:07.470
Well, I had a little trouble
in tinting class.

55:07.600 --> 55:10.880
In fact, I had a little trouble
in all my classes.

55:11.020 --> 55:14.350
Beauty school sure wasn't
what I thought it'd be.

55:14.480 --> 55:16.060
Nothing ever is.

55:19.910 --> 55:26.530
Vi? Erm, ... I dropped out.
What do you think of waitressing?

55:26.660 --> 55:28.620
You're too young to know.

55:29.500 --> 55:32.170
Maybe I could be
a telephone operator.

55:33.340 --> 55:37.170
No, I don't think I'd like to wear
those little things over my ears.

55:37.630 --> 55:43.010
God, if only I could have a guardian
angel to tell me what to do.

55:43.140 --> 55:46.760
Like Debbie Reynolds had in Tammy.
What do you think?

55:47.860 --> 55:50.530
If you find him,
give him my phone number.

